content.description: Another great sustained and overhanging route with large holds on Mr. Magoo Rock. The crux is sticking with it until the end.
content.protection: Six bolts and a two bolt anchor.
content.location: The route about five feet to the left of the arete on Mr. Magoo Rock.

content.description: A slight difficult start leads to overhanging climbing with interesting movement on large holds. One of the best 10's at the ranch.
content.protection: Six bolts and a two bolt anchor.
content.location: The second bolted route from the left hand side of Magoo Rock. There is a white streak near the bottom.

content.description: Just like all the other routes on this wall, this is a very sweet route.  This is the 3rd route from the left side of the wall, in between Mr. Magoo and Road Hog.  Sustained face climbing on a slightly overhanging wall makes this feel like a gym route, but oh so much better.
content.protection: 6 bolts, 2 bolt anchor with rap rings.

content.description: Start on the arete (right hand side) and climb up jugs to the anchor. The start will be harder for shorter people.
content.protection: Five bolts and a two bolt anchor.
content.location: Starts on the arete of Magoo rock and climbs right.

content.description: Boulder out the crux start then continue through slightly chossy rock to a challenging hand jam move pulling over a bulge.
content.location: Right and around the corner from The Flying Daisha.

content.description: Pull through the slightly overhanging start and cruise monster jugs to the anchor.
content.location: On the right side of Magoo Rock.

content.description: Sustained jug haul on steep rock.
content.protection: Five bolts and a two bolt anchor.
content.location: On the arete of Mr. Magoo Rock. The second route from the right. Shares a first bolt with Monkeys on Magoo.

content.description: Climb up to a huge ledge and begin the route from there.  The crux is down low then it goes to steep 5.10 climbing with big holds up top.  One move wonder..
content.location: Farthest left route on Magoo Rock.

content.description: Slide just left of the blunt arete, and flow up easy climbing to a crux below the anchors.
content.location: Right side of Magoo Rock to the right of Memoirs of a Daisha.

content.description: This is the boulder just left of Magoo Rock.   Needs scrubbing.    Obvious crimps on the far left of the rock. Sit-start from crimps into jugs. Move left when the wall blanks to an obvious left gaston and finish straight up.
content.protection: Pad. Little bit of a slope.

content.description: A free standing boulder which is littered with great features and holds some of the largest jugs at the ranch. If you can climb 5.9, you should check out Magoo Rock.
